      "solution": "input()\na = list(map(int, input().split()))\nb = [bin(i)[2:] for i in a]  # Convert all the numbers to binary. In Python, each binary\n# number comes with 0b at the front. So, to remove it we just take the binary string from index 2\nx = [i.rjust(len(max(b,key=lambda x: len(x))), '0') for i in b]\n# Now, we are justifying the binary string to the right by padding it with zeroes until we reach\n# the maximum length among all those binary strings.\ns=[]\nfor i in x:\n    r=i[1:-1].replace('1','_').replace('0','/\\\\')\n    # We choose charcters from index 1 till length of binary string - 2 to leave\n    # first and last characters and replace '1' by '_' and '0' by '/\\'\n    k=i[0]+i[-1]  # We take the first and last characters left out and modify them\n    k=k.replace('1','@').replace('0','$')  # as follows: '1' replaced with '@' and '0' by '$'\n    s.append(k[0]+r+k[-1])  # Now we append the modified first character, then the remaining transformed string\n    # and then the last character\nprint('\\n'.join(s))",
